The GDP figures for the second quarter are in. And they're looking good. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has averted a technical recession. According to Stats SA, the economy has grown in the second quarter READ: Mboweni's plan to save economy The GDP grew by 3.1-percent to rebound from a decrease in the first quarter. “Real gross domestic product (measured by production) increased by 3,1-percent in the second quarter of 2019, following a decrease of 3,1-percent in the first quarter of 2019,” said Statistician-General, Risenga Maluleke. READ: SA's economy declines in first quarter StatsSA, which released the latest gross domestic product data on Tuesday said mining, finance, trade and government services were the main drivers of growth. The construction, agriculture and transport sector, however, registered a slump in production.